<Content>Great Pool 5 stars standard, Beautiful hotel outside and inside, located next to the LaneCrawford shopping mall. The staff were friendly and professional. Tried their prize winning Italian restaurant and the lobby tea cafe, both were great.The bed are soft and comfortable, one of the best compare to other 5 stars hotel. Bathroom is huge and have a small TV installed. The only issue was water easily split out of the shower room, most of the time the floor are halfway wet.My friend recevied a hand written birthday card and a presnet suprisingly on his bday, we were not expecting that and that was very touching.The pool was fantastic and wonderful. Indoor, warm water, even had a overhead projected screen. However there was no life guard so someone may think that was not that safe. Towels were ready for you but be reminded about feet pool at the entrance, I accidentally step into the pool with the wool slippers and they were soaked with water for whole night!Ordered the in room breakfast but not as great as the one in Westin Financial Street. The room service food were good though, we had a burger, pizza and fruit plate and drinks.High-speed wireless internet everywhere in the hotel. Free one direction private car ride to Winland Center in the morning. 10 mins walk distance if you walk back. 
