<Content>Complete luxury in the heart of a busy city We visited Beijing for the first time and wanted to make sure we had good accomodations for our first trip to China. They had a great rate since the hotel was relatively new. We arranged to have a driver from the hotel pick us up at the airport so we would not have to deal with taxis (expensive but worth it). Upon arrival we upgraded to the club room which was a great decision. We came back from sightseeing to a relaxing atmosphere, a few snacks and refreshments. The ladies in the lounge were fantastic, writing the boys names for them in Chinese on red paper. They greated us every morning and evening as we came in.The rooms we excellent and the service was unbelievable. We stayed for 3 days then travelled to Guilin and and Xian. We left luggage at the Ritz and stayed there two nights on our return before we left China.The location was fine and we could get everywhere with a short taxi ride (taxi drivers are very nice). Very safe city and the people were also very friendly. The hotel restaurants were excellent as well.I would recommend this hotel 100% if you want a truly luxurious stay in Beijing. It really made the trip wonderful and they treated the boys great! 
