<Content>Fantastic stay at the Ritz! We stayed at the Ritz from March 1-March 8, 2008 for a family vacation with our two teenagers. I can't say enough good things about it and the staff there! The Ritz chain is our preference both in the US and abroad, and we've come to expect high standards from the hotels, but this one exceeded expectations. The property was very nice- we just had a standard room on the club level but it was quite large and beautifully appointed in what i'd call a modern Asian style. The staff were some of the nicest and most accomodating i've ever had the pleasure to meet, both in the club lounge and in all of the other areas of the hotel. They truly personalized the service there, which was pretty amazing considering the size of the hotel and the fact that it was quite busy with several business meetings while we were there. Great concierge staff- couldn't have been more helpful! The pool/spa area was calm and serene, really nice after a long day out battling the traffic in Beijing! The movie screen running old movies at the pool added an interesting touch! Everyone that we had contact with spoke English very well and all were so helpful to us. Our preferences in beverages, etc. were all remembered from the very first day- a small touch, but most appreciated! All in all, we had a wonderful experience there and I would highly recommend the Ritz Financial Street to both business and leisure travelers. 
