<Author>joy1
<Content>Great hotel Stayed here for one week October 25-November 1, 2007. We had pre-arranged with the hotel a private car for pickup at the airport. Cost of about $70 which is well worth the money given confusion and hassle once arriving in Beijing Airport. They greet you just as you depart the plane and escort you through customs. We were booked on the Club Floor and upgraded to an executive suite. A Club Floor representative was awaiting our arrival at the front desk and escorted us directly to our room, performing the formal check-in in the room. Rooms are spacious, exquisitely decorated and comfortable and housekeeping is impeccable. Club floor manager, Daniel, provides outstanding service to guests and ensures his staff does so, as well. Food presentation and atmosphere is one of the best in the R/C market. Ritz Carlton is known for outstanding service and this one doesn't disappoint, in fact went way beyond the expectation. I experienced a medical emergency on my first day and had to be taken to the hospital in an ambulance. Everyone from the hotel general manager, Mr. Flint, to the Rooms Manager, Mr. Militzer, were caring and understanding and couldn't do enough for us. They even sent their executive assistant in the ambulance to the hospital with us to ensure proper translation. She spent the entire day with us (Thank you, Lilian). Upon returning to my room from the hospital that evening, a beautiful bouquet of pink tea roses were awaiting me with a kind note from the management. They checked on us daily. How can you ask for more?Location is very convenient to all sight-seeing although plan ahead for time as Beijing traffic is worst than New York City. It could take you 1 hour to travel less than a mile, perhaps longer during rush hour. Smog is a problem in Beijing due to the traffic and volume of cars. Ritz Carlton Financial Street, you are the best!! 
