<Author>mux41
<Content>A Nice Stay Stayed in an 1200 sq ft executive suite for a week. There are one bed room, 1.5 bath and a huge living room in the suite with 3 seperate zones temp controls. They offer Bvlgari shampoo, bath gel and lotion in the suite. A fully automatic espresso machine with coffee beans and water filled was ready in the room so that we could have espresso coffee all the time. Bed was very comfortable. All curtains are electronically controlled. 42 plasma tvs in both the living room and bed room. a small screen lcd tv in the good size bathroom. We have been to the Qi and the Green Fish restaurants in the hotel. Qi offers Chinese foods and was not impressed. We went to Green Fish for the included buffet and lunch. Breakfast in Green Fish was the same everyday during our stay and it is not very impressive. Service in the Green Fish was soso as there were many occasions that when we came back to the table with a new plate of foods, the previously emptied plate was still on the table while a service person was standing not far away from the table smiling. So I actually prefer to have breakfast at the club lounge simply because the service is much nicer at the lounge although less choices were offered at the lounge. I heard the Cepe italian restaurant was nice, but we didn't have a chance to try that out. The lounge offers breakfast, all kinds of drinks including wine and beer and snacks from 6am to 10:30pm. Service persons were excellent in the lounge. We used the Concierge to reserve outside restaurants for us a couple time and they were very helpful and friendly. The general manager, Mr. Derek Flint, shows great leadership there as he was always around and even filled in the doorman's position to open the front door for us a couple times. We think the service will definitely improve in the near future. Swimming pool is nice sized and the water is warm enough. Changing rooms were well equipped. Exercise room is opened 24 hrs daily. Drawbacks: 1. since financial street is newly developed, there were not much around that area. A new mall right next to the RC will be opened in Aug and this should improve. 2. You almost always need to take a taxi when going out though the taxi is cheap in China. Be aware that most taxi drivers expect hotel guests to go long distance (airport etc). We had a couple times asking them to go to places not far away and felt that they were not happy and complaining. Overall this is a nice hotel. We would definitely come back to this hotel in the future when we visit Beijing again. 
