<Author>vandelaak
<Content>Great stay! We stayed at this Ritz-Carlton property at the end of 2006, the last week of December to be precise. The hotel was and is (brand) new, and truly wonderful. It is very stylish and modern, business like. The room was VERY spacious, the beds are comfortable, the large bathroom has separate bath and shower facilities and there is a little TV which you can watch while you are bathing! I stayed with my wife and little daughter, the staff were extremely helpful and friendly. My daughter got a lovely panda bag, bath toys and Mickey mouse baby night light... and a little Santa Clause doll as well! Courtesy from the Ritz-Carlton. Very nice gesture, one of Ritz-Carlton's signature services! The room has a big wide flat screen tv, which is nice. Breakfast is wonderful with lots of choices. In the main lobby there are local young ladies in traditional dresses playing Chinese instruments. Very relaxing to listen to. We didn't go to the Spa, since we went out exploring Beijing. Location wise the hotel is not in the centre (it will take around 40 minutes from the airport to go to the hotel by taxi, only RMB 90) There are not many restaurant in this area, although the concierge can recommend you one, but you will have to take a taxi. The hotel is located in a financial district, in the immediately area there are no things noteworthly regarding sightseeing. When you look out of the window you will basically see a relaxing business district view. (office buildings and broad roads, some greenery, nice spacious) All major sightseeing locations are within 10 - 20 minutes distances by car. For example the Imperial Palace is only 10 minutes away by car. Make sure you bring along a little namecard of the hotel, in case the driver, which is most likely, doesn't know the hotel. (because it is so new, most of the taxi drivers don't know it yet... and most of them, if not all, don't know any English, but they are friendly though) There is a shopping mall with the MacDonalds nearby and a very nice big supermarket in the basement. Great for buying some snacks. Around 10 minutes walking distance. I really recommend this hotel if you are looking for a stylish retreat. I'm a hotelier myself... so you can trust me. Enjoy. 
